verses.verse: To the chief<WH5329> Musician,<WH5329> A Psalm<WH4210> and Song<WH7892> of David.<WH1732> Praise<WH8416> waits<WH1747> for you, O God,<WH430> in Sion:<WH6726> and to you shall the vow<WH5088> be performed.<WH7999>
O you that hear<WH8085> prayer,<WH8605> to you shall all<WH3605> flesh<WH1320> come.<WH935>
Iniquities<WH1697> <WH5771> prevail<WH1396> against me: as for our transgressions,<WH6588> you shall purge<WH3722> them away.

Blessed<WH835> is the man whom you choose,<WH977> and cause to approach<WH7126> to you, that he may dwell<WH7931> in your courts:<WH2691> we shall be satisfied<WH7646> with the goodness<WH2898> of your house,<WH1004> even of your holy<WH6918> temple.<WH1964>

By terrible<WH3372> things in righteousness<WH6664> will you answer<WH6030> us, O God<WH430> of our salvation;<WH3468> who are the confidence<WH4009> of all<WH3605> the ends<WH7099> of the earth,<WH776> and of them that are afar<WH7350> off on the sea:<WH3220>
Which by his strength<WH3581> sets<WH3559> fast the mountains;<WH2022> being girded<WH247> with power:<WH1369>
Which stills<WH7623> the noise<WH7588> of the seas,<WH3220> the noise<WH7588> of their waves,<WH1530> and the tumult<WH1995> of the people.<WH3816>
They also that dwell<WH3427> in the uttermost<WH7098> parts are afraid<WH3372> at your tokens:<WH226> you make the outgoings<WH4161> of the morning<WH1242> and evening<WH6153> to rejoice.<WH7442>

You visit<WH6485> the earth,<WH776> and water<WH7783> it: you greatly<WH7227> enrich<WH6238> it with the river<WH6388> of God,<WH430> which is full<WH4390> of water:<WH4325> you prepare<WH3559> them corn,<WH1715> when you have so<WH3651> provided<WH3559> for it.

You water<WH7301> the ridges<WH8525> thereof abundantly:<WH7301> you settle<WH5181> the furrows<WH1417> thereof: you make it soft<WH4127> with showers:<WH7241> you bless<WH1288> the springing<WH6780> thereof.
You crown<WH5849> the year<WH8141> with your goodness;<WH2896> and your paths<WH4570> drop<WH7491> fatness.<WH1880>
They drop<WH7491> on the pastures<WH4999> of the wilderness:<WH4057> and the little hills<WH1389> rejoice<WH1524> on every side.<WH2296>
The pastures<WH3733> are clothed<WH3847> with flocks;<WH6629> the valleys<WH6010> also are covered<WH5848> over<WH5848> with corn;<WH1250> they shout<WH7321> for joy, they also<WH637> sing.<WH7891>
